- So they are flip up....but why are both pairs of lenses diffraction? - When you flip them up, they will hold and stay up as long as you're not raging too hard. If you're bouncing up and down, they will flip back down. So it almost defeated my purpose of popping out the regular frame lens.

I am new to Patty and went on a bit of a shopping spree last week when I saw all the great tops for winter!! This was one of them. For your reference with regard to my photos, here are my 'stats':

34 y/o
5'7"
135lbs
34A bra size (I know, I know...)

I normally wear small or medium for my blouse size (more medium than small). In terms of my body shape, have broad shoulders, a long torso, longish lean arms, an hour glass waist but disproportionately large hips and booty booty. While I certainly can't see my abs, my stomach is probably a little flatter than the average woman's but I do have some love (hate) handles.

OK, now that all of that fun stuff is out of the way, here's my review of this top. It arrived on time, and packaged very nicely! The color matched the pictures online which I always really appreciate. For the most part I was really pleased with the fit!

Usually when I buy a top in size medium, it isn't quite as form fitting as this is. That's not a problem, it's just not the norm for me. Having tried on a handful of Patty tops now I can say confidently that I would feel uncomfortable in a small (in spite of my Dixie cup bra size). Be prepared that these tops/sweaters are really going to fit your form in whatever your normal size is. For that reason, I highly recommend ordering up a size if you're in doubt, unless of course you are built like the model (congratulations!), enjoy showing off your muffin top for all to see, or are planning to use major cleavage to distract eyes from looking at your midsection. Unfortunately I don't have cleavage. Even if I did, I'm more modest by nature, so I plan to wear this top with a cami.  That being said, the thicker fabric of this cardigan (unlike other Patty tops) will hide a multitude of "sins" haha.  So even if you've got a little pudge around the middle, it's not going to show.

Beyond that, I really love this sweater! The fabric is soft and feels quality. The sleeves and torso are luxuriously long!! I can't tell you how refreshing it is to buy a sweater/top that is long enough for me in both the arms AND torso with length to spare!! Shorter women with shorter arms may struggle with all of these Patty tops just because they're so long. You may end up needing to fold or hem.  The pockets are actual pockets (not just faux pockets) but they are itty bitty.  Don't plan on actually using them much.

To sum up, I love the look and style of this sweater and think it could be worn in a lot of different ways!  I'm so happy to have found Patty Boutik! I LOVE the style and the quality and I can't wait to wear my new fall/winter wardrobe! Hopefully this is helpful for someone else. If it is, check out my reviews for several other PB garments!
summary: Love this cardigan!!  Flattering for any body type!!

reviewText: Love it. I'm glad I bought it

I am a big fan now of Patty Boutik products, and this sweater was no different. Very nice quality, and fit was very nice as with all of her other products. I probably have about 8 or 9 items of hers, and love all of them.

As it turns out, this product was a bit more snug than expected, but not so much so that I couldn't wear it. It is also a lot longer than the fit for the model. I assume this is because I have a shorter torso/am a shorter person in general. It goes all the way down past my hips/behind.

My recommendation is that if you are a shorter person/have a shorter torso, but want the model's look, not to purchase this item. If you don't care that this is longer, then it is a really nice, thick sweater.

The only thing that I don't like about this sweater is that the buttons are brown instead of black, but I can replace them at a later date.

reviewText: This wallet is all kinds of awesome. It goes great with my Loungefly duffle. It fits all my cards and still has room for more. If you're a Star Wars fan this is a must buy!!!
Bought for my best friends Christmas gift....it is perfect! Super cute and worth the money
very cute
High quality.

I asked for this for Christmas based on looks alone, and luckily, my "only look at the main picture" purchasing strategy worked out this time. The wallet feels leather-like and durable, and I love the zipper feature--nothing falls out! Cards fit snugly into the pockets inside; you might be able to squeeze two cards in a pocket, but there is no cramming four gift cards into one card pocket with this wallet. There is space on both sides of the coin pouch for cash or more cards. The coin pouch itself zippers nicely and is closed at the bottom so coins won't fall out into the bill space. It isn't made to hold as much change as my last wallet, but seeing as I don't tend to cart around tons of nickels and pennies with me, this doesn't bother me. The one downside is that, as the picture of the interior shows, your ID is going to be hard to get out. The bottom card pocket on one side has a clear front, so it's meant to be the spot for your driver's license...but have fun getting to it. Since the wallet doesn't open up flat, you can't just flip out the pocket and flash your ID while still in the wallet. You have to pry the actual card out. For me, this is a noticeable inconvenience, but not enough of one to make me regret the purchase or not want to use the wallet.

Overall--great quality and ought to last a long time, holds an adequate amount of wallet-y stuff, and yay Star Wars!
summary: Fun and well-made, but getting to your ID could be easier.

Great, modest swim wear. Includes lined underwear which is a huge plus! Runs a bit small, and even smaller for a little girl with hips and a booty but a tiny waist. They are cute straight, and real draw string, so not for curvy girls, but they will work for this summer for us. They are a little shorter than board shorts, but still modestly long.

Exactly what we were looking for to replace the boys board shorts my daughter wore last summer. She wears between a 3T and 4T, 38" tall and about 35lbs, and the 3T were actually roomy around the waist. But unlike other name brand shorts, they adjust to fit her without gapping front or back. And perhaps the coolest feature, they have a panty lining as part of the shorts. So if your little one is potty training or trained, you don't have to put on a swim bottom underneath. So for days of light swimming but heavy sand play at the beach, your daughter can wear these to decrease the amount of sand that gets in, and shells won't scratch her legs when sitting. We are officially huge fans and will continue to get these shorts in the future.
summary: Exactly how I might have designed board shorts for my daughter.

While the title description is misleading, I actually like what I bought. However, it's not a coat in the traditional sense of what you might think a coat is, least of all a trench coat. It's a jacket, more like a suit jacket or a blazer. I expected a long coat and ended up with a suit jacket, so at first I was a little disappointed. But the material is comfortable, and rather than having a button to close the jacket there is a snap instead. Different, but doable. I also like the fold gray collar and sleeve on the navy blue; it's different.

Since it's from, I believe, a Chinese clothing company it's often best to buy one to two sizes higher than what you usually wear. I used their recommended size chart and worked it out easily. I also suspect since the company is foreign maybe this is a long coat for the people's sizes in that country even if it isn't for my need. It may be the same for someone else who chooses to purchase this product.

I could have returned it, but I ended up liking what I received. If you want a fall/winter jacket you can mostly likely mix around with your Sunday best or casual clothes, check this out. It wasn't that expensive. But if you want something like a peacoat or an actual trench, this product is most likely not for you.
summary: It's A Jacket, Not A Long Coat

After waiting a long, cold month for these gloves, I nearly freaked when I tried them on and they initially didn't fit. They had just come in from being left on my porch. After pacing and fretting a bit, I tried them on again and they made a tight fit but seem to be improving with use. Be aware they run small. My hands are on the small side of medium and it took a lot of wiggling for them to fit. They are warm and the leather seems to be good quality. But take very seriously their shipping estimate because they aren't overstating the wait as sometimes Amazon does. (They can sometimes say 3-5 days and it comes in 2.) The color is accurate and will go well with most medium to dark blues. But these are not navy gloves, which was something I was trying to avoid. Bows are attached securely also, which was  concern of mine. Overall, a good product if you have patience. With single digit temps while I waited, I want very patient. It would be nice if the Chinese company kept a small amount of stock in the U.S. for the impatient Americans, but economics may not allow that. They lost a star on the small sizing and the long wait, but they're a good pair of gloves.
summary: Order Early; Gloves Come On A Slow Boat From China

Over the years, I've bought more handbags than I can count. This style is, by far my all-time favorite.

I bought my Norah elsewhere in a different color, so I can only speak about the style rather than this particular color.

First of all, this is a big bag, not a medium, so if you don't want something big, this is not the bag for you. I love the fact that the bag is a tall one, and that it has one big compartment. That way, I can open it up wide enough in order to see everything inside. This bag could easily hold my Kindle Fire HD 8.9 tablet if I wanted to carry it, plus a lot more.

I like the two pen holders, as I use one for a pen, and another for my stylus. My LG V10, which is a big phone, fits in one of the two smaller compartments, so it's protected and easy to find. The larger zippered compartment is very roomy, and it holds everything I need it to hold.

I'm a shoulder strap-kind of person, and the strap in this bag is long enough, and it's wide. I really hate it when manufacturers put thin shoulder straps on big bags!

I also like the little "feet" on the bottom of the bag. They just add some extra protection when it has to sit on the floor.

I have two suggestions for Brahmin. Please put an outside pocket on your bags. Also, please tone down the gold. A brushed gold would make the bag look more refined and elegant.

reviewText: Purchased for my husband, he loves them!

ThinOptics reading glasses are a great idea, poorly executed.  The idea is great:  reading glasses that fold up inside a small sleeve attached to your phone, so you don't have to carry separate glasses.  But there are problems.  The first problem is that it is difficult to get them to fit comfortably and snugly on your nose.  I find that the glasses constantly move around or fall off.  The second problem is that the bridge (the part that attaches the glasses to your nose) is flimsy.  After using the glasses for awhile, one of the bridge pieces deteriorated, came loose, and ultimately fell off.
The third problem is the lack of customer service.  I have been unable to get a customer service rep on the phone, and the ThinOptics website says that they are experiencing a large call and email volume.  And it's not like the glasses are cheap. Very disappointed.
summary: Flimsy product, poor fit, no customer service

This is my original review but please be sure to see newly added info:  I ordered this case for my daughter as she collects giraffes. She had seen this cover at the mall and begged me to buy it but it was so expensive there that I just couldn't spend that kind of money, twenty bucks, on it but I knew I could probably find one here and I did.  I was surprised when it arrived that it's really more of a cover than a case.  It's a soft rubber like cover that just slips right onto the back of the phone.  It fits perfectly and doesn't make the phone bulky like some case/covers do.  I was pleasantly surprised with the shipping time as I expected it to take much longer since it's coming from Asia but it got here in about two weeks.  Nice cover and pleased the recipient and the buyer! Do keep in mind that it's transparent somewhat so the phone color will show through. Looks nice on her black phone.
NEW INFORMATION: Just a day after I posted this review, I noticed my daughter had tape on her phone.  Turns out that while all of the above was true in that it does fit well, isn't bulky, looks cute on her black phone and the shipping time was shorter than expected, that's not enough to overcome the biggest problem.  IT FELL COMPLETELY APART AFTER ONE WEEK.  It started on the top corner then the bottom...the plastic just split and began peeling away from the original shape. Granted, my kid is a typical teen in that her phone is with her 24/7, it still should have lasted longer. It may be fine for someone like myself who doesn't use the phone near as often, but I can't give this a good rating.  You really do get what you pay for!

What I love about it is that it's very comfortable and it's a little on the heavier side (which was a plus for me because I got married in the winter). The ONLY minor issue (which is easily correctable) is that if you're smaller than a B-cup, or have a shorter torso (such as myself), the dress will not hold up very well in the bust-area. If you tighten the back just enough though, it can pull it close enough to your chest to not really be a problem. If you have a local tailor that would obviously be the better option (but if you bought the dress last-minute like I did it helps).
I would definitely recommend it to anybody looking for a simple, short, easy-to-dress-up kind of gown!

reviewText: This is the BEST TEN DOLLAR WIG you're going to buy. I'm not saying it's PERFECT or anything but it's a really great wig for the price. It does tangle after a little bit but it's not that bad. I have a kind of big head and it fits okay but i have to pull it so my hair line won't show. The hair falls out a little but if you're gentle it shouldn't be a problem, overall i love what I got and it exceeded my expectations for ten dollars. Again I'm not saying it's as good as a $150 wig and if you are looking for something for everyday wear I WOULD NOT recommend it. However, if you are just looking for something fun and cute and don't want to invest big money into something, this is the way to go. I just wear it when I'm making YouTube videos so I don't have to worry about my own hair. quick and easy. If you want to see it in my videos go find my YouTube channel: Rikkana The Fairy.

I wanted to like this product, but had 2 negative deal breakers:

1) The product just doesn't work. I wish I could return it, but due to travel and the delayed delivery, I couldn't return it in time for a refund. The punch is SUPER difficult to press - requires a lot of force. I couldn't get it to work at all (even on a piece of paper so it's the tool itself that's having trouble), but the gift recipient tried and got it to work with all his strength. When it finally did punch, we couldn't get the collar stay to come out in one piece. It kept on punching in half rather than as a full collar stay (which of course makes it useless). It's also dangerous - when he finally got it to work, the two pieces flew out and almost poked me in the eye. I'm hoping the one I got is a fluke given that the other reviews are good, but I definitely would not recommend.

2) I ordered it with expedited shipping to get here in time for a gift, but what I received was an empty box. The box hadn't been tampered with and seemed to be in perfect condition, but was empty. Turns out, this was an Amazon error (rather than from Pick Punch LLC). I called Amazon and Pick Punch LLC and both were nice about getting me another shipment and waiving the next expedited fee. Still delayed my gift giving and took away some of the oomph.

This is a must for Attack on Titan fans! I bought one recently and it's comfortable (and looks awesome)! There's just few things you want to do before you buy this product:

1: The measurements on the description are way off. Make sure you buy "2" sizes up. I normally wear a Medium in men's, so I ordered the X-Large jacket. It fit me just perfect!

2: When you initially get the jacket in the mail, be sure to zipper it up and fold it "inside-out" before you wash it. There is a lot of leftover fur inside the jacket, hence why I folded it inside-out. make sure to do this every time you wash it to prevent the logo from fading/scratching.

3: The Zipper. Be gentle with it whenever you zipper it up. It's not the highest quality zipper, but if your careful with it,it will last quite a while.

That pretty much sums up my review; I don't normally order clothes online, but I couldn't pass up this jacket (it was too cool!!!). I hope you find this review helpful, cheers
summary: Awesome Jacket, Just take a Note of a few things

reviewText: I purchased this set of collars because the spring-style ones my gym has are overstretched and don't securely hold the plates on the bar. reviewText:
So I ordered this top before reading the reviews, which I normally don't do, and as I waited for it to arrive I started to get nervous after reading several reviews that stated it ran small. I am probably between a medium and a large in American sizes, and I tend to get a large since I don't like things that are very tight. I ordered a large and it fits great, honesty I could have probably gotten a medium and it would have fit (although maybe a little snug).
As another reviewer mentioned, there is no way to wear it as a dress as pictured on the model- I'm short (5"1") and the lace top layer falls right under my butt, the black under layer stops at about the middle of my butt. That doesn't bother me since I didn't intend to wear it as a dress anyways. I have tried it with leggings and a pair of skinny tan dress pants and it looks good with both.
I read a review that mentioned the top was shear- which is partially true. the layer under the lace is definitely translucent so parts of your body that presses against the fabric maybe at least partially visible. For me this is only a problem at the bust, when I first tried it on I was wearing a light colored bra with a pattern and I could make out the bra pattern through the shirt. Easy fix, I just wear a black bra or a black tank top underneath and I'm good.
Yet another review mentioned the tight arms- this worried me most of all cause I have wide shoulders but the shoulder area of the top has plenty of space. The sleeves do get tighter below the elbow but the lace does have some stretch to it so there is some give to it.
Now that the shirt has arrived I am actually kind of happy I didn't read the reviews first because if I had I probably would not have bought it which would have been a shame 'cause it is a very cute top. I may buy it in red as well.
Very pretty and fits perfectly.

I ordered my normal size and it fit perfectly. It is absolutely too short to wear as a dress like in the picture. I am 5'5 and I had to wear leggings with it. I figured this would be the case so I was not disappointed. I would still recommend. I received a lot of compliments when I wore it.

I like to start all my reviews in the middle - that is three stars. I add a star for exceptional quality. I add a star for exceptional customer service. Good quality, engineering/design and function also rate a star - Stars are subtracted if any of the above items are severely lacking. Given that, this is how I rate this watch:

FORTES
- Good looks, highly adjustable, and great quality

FOIBLES
- This band is sans any attachment pins
- Difficult to remove for a man - even after 'greasing' catch tab with Vaseline....
  Nearly impossible for the average woman to remove

While the watchband is difficult for my wife to attach, she does like the looks. She just has to have me, or a flat-bladed screwdriver to remove the band. The watchband attaches to itself with two hooks on the rear underside of of the hasp - These hooks attach to a bar, which is part of the length adjustment section. I told my wife she needs to hold the top up and back - like a viper getting ready to strike. in order to allow the unseen hooks (from the wearer's perspective) to attach to the perpendicular bar.

Recommended with Caution

reviewText: Low cost way to have fun tagging your luggage. I travel a lot and have yet to see anyone with the same tags. Fun characters that have gotten compliments from other travelers. I slid my business card in each one to act as my contact info.

For the price, they are fine. The materials are cheap plastic but they are rugged and durable; I don't feel like either the tag or loop are likely to break from being thrown around. The plastic loop is attached by plastic nubs on a strip stuck through holes on the other side of the strip, and it has good staying power but can be easily undone compared to other luggage tags. After a good bit of use I've found that the weak spot is that the plastic loops will pop undone every once in awhile if you catch a tag at an odd angle under something heavy, like another piece of luggage, and pry the loop at an odd angle while trying to pick up your luggage out of a pile. It's not a frequent issue but has happened to me twice now, no damage to the tag/loop though. Another downside is that the paper inserts are not protected from rain, which could get to be a pain if you travel a lot. But if you don't mind the risk of one getting lost or ruined, you get 20 of them. And the bright green is nice, true to color in the picture.

reviewText: Love the quality
Nice wallet
I always like zipperred wallets. This is the best so far.

I am a girl and I like men's wallets. They are smaller, more practical, more discreet and just plain nicer. I don't want a shiny, huge, pink wallet that will carry the kitchen sink (as a girl, in theory, I have a handbag that can do that -- but I don't, either): I want a to-the-point wallet that will take currency, credit cards, my driver's license and a couple of receipts. No coins, no checkbook, no whatever else women carry in those huge wallets. And on days when for some reason I don't carry a handbag, they will fit into my front jeans pocket or interior coat pocket.

I've been using zippered wallets for years, for the simple reason that I like it that stuff never falls out (I can do a great job of misplacing cash and credit cards on my own, thank you). There have been previous incursions into Amazon's apparently bottomless stash of zippered wallets. The wallets were okay, but with too many divisions, pockets, little nooks and crannies that ended up making them too large, too thick, too bulky, too complicated. And one of them had way too much padding, so even empty it felt huge.

Enter the Mancini wallet. It is zippered. It is small. It has RFID -- I'd been using those little RFID envelopes for my credit cards, but an RFID wallet is so much more practical, especially because the envelopes have a nasty habit of falling apart. The compartments are perfect for me (and you can even remove the insert if you want to keep it VERY simple). It has two billfolds, something I always want because I travel a lot and can keep different currencies organized. The leather is soft and supple and the two-toned detail looks classy. Everything is well aligned and sewn together, and the zipper looks like it will last.

This may well be my wallet for a long time to come.

I considered returning this product, but it hardly seemed worth it for the price paid.

The image used doesn't show a serious flaw in this product: the "pearls" used are not solid. They are the the ones with holes drilled for stringing. So, the necklace looks much cheaper up close. That said, from across a table, it's probably not noticeable. But I noticed immediately, and felt like it looked incredibly cheap (which--in all fairness--it was).

The first flaw I noticed upon opening was that the necklace I received did not have a chain to adjust the length (as pictured on the sale page). It is barely long enough to close. To be able to wear this necklace comfortably, I would need to add several links to the chain. It hardly seems worth it for the necklace, so I have yet to do so.

It's a lovely design concept, and if you don't mind something that looks rather costumey up close, and only appears classy from across a room (such as for stage jewelry or to go with an actual costume), this could be good for you.

I will--most likely--cannibalize the parts for some other craft, such as a picture frame or some other household craft.

I'm still giving 4 stars because based on a price point under $5, I don't think it's fair to rate this product against much higher quality jewelry. I deducted a star because of the chain being incomplete/broken/not a represented by the seller, and because I cannot say that I "love it" or would order it again. That said... for $4, it's not horrible.

And who knows... I might actually wear the earrings one day...
summary: About what you'd expect for under $5

reviewText: I just received it.  It's just as pictured.  I feel it will work for what I expect it to.  Satisfied!
soo me.

Hi All,

I received this bag from family as a gift 2 years ago now.  I have not used it as a daily bag but more of an occasional travel bag -- when I need it for a road trip or quick stay at the family house.  I also use it every now and again as a gym bag.  Let me just say, this is an exceptional piece of equipment for the money.  When I first opened it 2 years ago, it did have a funny smell.  That dissipated over a week, and of course has not since returned.  The piece feels very durable for the price and many (Read ALL) people are fooled into thinking it is leather.  Other reviewers that comment on its shininess --- there are nice quality leathers out there that shine just like this.  When it first arrived, yes, a bit too shiny, but as it has aged, it has begun to really fool people.

Pros:
*Very Handsome
*High Quality zippers seem to slide with ease
*Looks like leather
*Arrives quickly, and well packaged

Cons:
*This is a cheap bag -- please do not expect it to hold up if you mistreat it and abuse it like you would a normal leather bag.  This needs a bit more care to make it last longer but with the extra $300 i saved by not buying a saddleback, I think its very much worth it.
summary: Great bag, treat it with care and it will be 5 stars

reviewText: I have been wearing this coat for approximately 6 weeks so I think I can give a pretty good review.  For the pros, this coat is adorable and fits me well.  It is long enough to keep my back door warm.  I am 5'3" and 125 lbs and the medium fits me perfect.  I love the belt and the zipper seems to be of good quality.  I got the red one and the color is a very nice shade of lipstick red.  I also love how there is that built-in hand covering.  I wish more designers did this.  For the cons, there is no down inside this coat - it is just a polyester fill so it is warm but not to the extent I was expecting.  The inner lining has also split at the seam exposing the polyester fill.  The hood is also a problem.  That gray flap that looks so cute on the model hangs down over my eyes.  I guess I could consider it a visor to keep down-coming snow out, but then I can't see where I am going and risk walking into a drift.  I have to fold it back in order for the hood to function as it should.  Very cute but overpriced with a cheap lining and problematic hood.  I would not buy again.

reviewText:
I have owned and come across many watches through the years. That being said, this is my first mono-hand watch, so the experience is quite unique and does require some time to get used to.
I have been contemplating on buying a mono-hand watch for a while, and having settled on the Botta brand, I have to say was treading to unknown territory. The other brands that I was considering were Meistersinger, Defakto and Danish Design.
The Meistersinger was dropped due to the hefty price tag of its models. Defakto offered a beautiful mono-hand under the "Eins" range. It's uncluttered and clean dial is a superb example of the minimal Bauhaus design. But the 42mm and protruding lugs would look ridiculously large on my average wrist (7.2"). So that was dropped. There was the striking and lovely looking mono-hand watches from Danish Design, very minimal and clean. However, the price was a bit steep for such a  brand and the dial and bezel combination that I wanted wasn't available. So Botta it was.
Now, the next big question was which UNO version should I opt for, the 40mm or 44mm? I have an average wrist and have owned watches that have a diameter between 38mm to 42mm. The usual decision would have been the 40mm, given my wrist size. However, something kept on nagging me to get the 44mm, so the 44mm it was.
The watch arrived two days later, placed snugly in foam which was within a cylinder. The packaging is very eye catching and unique. Very well thought out and efficient. It all echoes the brand's minimal approach to design, which I find to be refreshing.
The watch appeared to be a bit intimidating at first, given the wide white dial and space. However, given the lugless and flat design, the watch rests comfortably on smaller wrists. The more I look at the dial, the more I'm convinced that I made the right choice for selecting the 44mm. There's no way to precisely tell the time in a mono-hand watch in small dial. The generous wide face lends a hand in telling time more accurately.
My only gripe with this watch would be the supplied leather band. It's one of those stiff type leather that's not malleable which tends to show cracks quickly. Oddly, it adds to the large size of the watch on an average sized wrist. A quick change of the band to a suede leathered strap helps a lot and enhances the experience.
The watch I have now is actually a replacement to the watch I received earlier. I was adjusting the time when the crown came loose. I requested a replacement and received one the next day. The seller is very prompt, attentive and very accommodating. An added plus for a new watch experience, especially that of the mono-hand. This watch is a welcome addition to my timepiece collection. Definitely a keeper that adds a more relaxed approach to time measurement.
summary: A Different Approach to Tell Time...A Relaxed One

One good thing about this cuff is it softens up over time the more you wear it and becomes even more comfortable.  At the same time- the one I received did not soften up so much that the tip became floppy no matter which hole I put the pin into.  If you want to keep it supple I'd recommend storing it in the closed position- buckled up in the same hole that you wear it in most often when it's on your wrist.  If you find it doesn't fit quite as you like- but want the same look- the leather in this cuff is thick enough that you can add an extra hole or two  into it if done carefully; or you can wear this one notch looser than you usually would.  The one I got stayed stiff enough that it doesn't slide around much even if you wear it looser and do not happen to have the wrist of a body builder. (as most don't)  The cuff looks better in person than it does in the picture...the contrast between the leather and metal works well and doesn't scream LOOK AT MY WRIST THERE'S SOMETHING DIFFERENT ON MY WRIST as you might think from the picture.  Seems well made though keep In mind any leather can dry out and crack over time and adding conditioner paste to a cuff that isn't plain might not be worth the mess.  But overall if you want to bulk out your wriist or accessorize with other black items you wear this is probably a good choice cuff.  Hope this helps

I ordered this dress for a wedding. All of the bridesmaids are wearing different navy dresses. I was disappointed that this dress isn't the navy I expected from the picture. In dark lighting it could probably pass for navy, but in sunlight or well-lit rooms it is almost a cobalt or electric blue.
The dress has a sheen to it that cheapens the look. However, the fit is beautiful. It accentuates all the right places and the price was right. I may or may not use it for this wedding (will have to see it with the other girls' dresses) but will likely keep it for nights out with my husband or for other weddings where I'm a guest. (I uploaded a photo. Notice the color on the left hip where the sunlight is hitting.)
summary: Not truly navy, but a beautiful fit.

reviewText: I bought the dress in both the red and the Navy because I feel jewel tones flatter me and I read one user's comment that the Navy was lighter than pictured and another said that it was really more of an electric blue.  If you like red, then the red will do it for you, but I didn't like it as much.  The blue was much more flattering.  However, it was disappointing for me because it really was a navy.  Not the fault of the seller, who said it was Navy.  The darker color may be also beneficial for those who are looking for something that will disguise bulges better than say the brighter red.  Additionally, I will echo other users and say that you couldn't ask for more regarding the comfort level of this dress.  For me, I'm not sure if it's quite what I'm looking for - for this particular occasion.
summary: This Just May Be Your Dress

reviewText:
Nice and sturdy, well constructed.  Sizing IS off a bit, mine said 49.2" and was actually 48" from end to end, 46" not including buckle.

No issues with the buckle popping open as some have suggested....but see how it COULD be an issue for some people.  The tradition "slide" mechanism found on most nylon belts might have been a better option, but like I said, it hasn't been an issue for me.

This belt doe appear to run shorter than advertised, so if you are towards the higher end of the size, I'd recommend getting the next larger size.  There are multiple listings for this same belt, and one DOES offer multiple sizes. If belt is too long, you can either send back for replacement or trim to size, and melt the end.

Shipping was fast, packaging was fine. I really like the look and feel.  Heavy and well constructed. Thats the good stuff. I really like the buckle overall but it is so disappointing. The big downfall is the design. The locking lever swings the wrong way so any strain on the buckle like picking up something heavy or just pulling on the belt causes it to pop open, so I  am constantly re-buckling my belt while I work. Unfortunately I will be finding a replacement.

reviewText:
I bought this top searching for products I could use as baselayers under my work clothes; I'm in the process of picking out gym clothes I can wear under my work clothes so I waste less time changing at the gym.

The fabric is attractive and the top appears well-constructed but I will have to return the top due to the fit.

While the top fits well around my chest and shoulders (it could be tighter, but I think I'd get enough support from the shelf bra) the fabric scrunches too much around my torso to be discreetly worn under anything. That said, it's also not loose enough that I would attempt any sort of activity where I'd be anticipating a serious sweat--the fabric is thick and while that's great for support and diminishing the "headlight effect" there is no way you'd be able to seriously sweat in this thing and move on to any less intensive activity without being seriously uncomfortable. I might consider it if the top fit tightly, but with the bunching up there's no way this thing could accomplish any sort of wicking action.

This top might be for you if you're a bigger size and looking for something you could wear as a base layer for cold weather activities where you wouldn't be sweating intensively or as your primary top if you won't build up a serious sweat.

For a reference, I'm 5'4", 33" chest and 26" waist.
summary: Well made but with very particular fit.

This workout top is incredibly comfortable. The fabric almost glides over your skin! The other aspect that makes this so comfortable is how the design of the built in sports bra. Instead of the standard thin band on the bottom, there is a thick elastic band. This makes you forget there is even a sports bra underneath.

The sizing is off on this though. I wear a medium sized shirt. After seeing other reviews saying it ran small, I ordered a large/x-large shirt. The shirt is extremely tight on me. I'm still able to put it on, but it is very tight. My daughter wears a women's size small. This shirt was comfortable on her. It was tight, but slightly baggy. Basically on my daughter, the shirt had wiggle room.

The quality on the shirt is excellent. The stitching is done with a surged edge and is very tightly done. The surged edges are firmly attached to the shirt which makes it not irritate my skin. After carefully examining the shirt, I did not see any rips, tears or fraying anywhere on this shirt. The fabric is thick, but does allow some ventilation. It is also very flattering when you wear it.

Overall, I would recommend this shirt. I just recommend that you pay attention to sizing and order a size or two up. The quality of this shirt is incredible. The material and design make it extremely comfortable. I did receive this at a discounted or free rate for my honest and unbiased opinion, but all opinions expressed are my own.
summary: Extremely comfortable, but order a size larger!

I thought this item was very poorly made. It has loose ends that were not tied off. It was also covered in pieces of red yarn, which had to be removed piece by piece. The important issue with this review, is that it is allowed to be read by other customers, and not pulled by Amazon as "an issue I need to contact the seller about!" It is NOT my dissatisfaction with an item I did not like due to just poor quality.  Nor is it about receiving a complicated return process.  I believe items such as this should have a strict code that needs to be passed before selling to any consumer.  I know this and other like items are a health hazard. Here is why;  I could not get the smell of pesticides out of the garment.  I have had this happen before and did look into what the smell was. It smells very similar to diesel or petrol and sometimes it is a combination of all these things. I knew the minute I opened the package what I was dealing with. I cannot have any such item near me due to the odor, which exacerbates my migraines. There are many pesticides that are legal in other countries that are NOT legal in the USA. Beware if you are allergy prone or just do not want something as dangerous as poison next to your skin. It is also highly flammable. I left this sweater outside in below zero degree temps for days and it still smelled just as strong when I brought it back into the house. I would warm customers buying from foreign countries as this is not the first time I have had this problem with items (especially anything made from yarn or wool) having this heavy smell.  I was contacted by email stating I could get a refund if I went through a complicated return process. I am more concerned about the health and safety of others and will not be spending my time going through this that and the other to return something I believe to not only be a very poorly made product but one that makes me ill to even have it in my home. I wrapped it in the packaging it came in, and deposited the nasty thing into last weeks trash. The sweater not only smells of chemicals but it was not easy getting the smell off my hands after touching it. There is actually a greasy feel to the yarn. Beware of these products. I
summary: Beware of products smelling of diesel, that smell is more likely pesticides!

Fyi - I am NOT one of those paid to post people.  I bought these because I wanted some cheap (but polarized) sunglasses for being outside in the summer.  Polarized is a must for me as I like how they cut the glare.  But I also don't like to spend a lot on sunglasses for being by the pool or cutting the grass bc I'm likely to mess them up.  These are exactly what I was looking for - inexpensive polarized lenses.  The metal of the frames is very light - probably pretty susceptible to being broken or smooshed but the glasses wholly lived up to my expectations.  They sit lightly on my face.  I'd say lens color appears pretty much as advertised and I checked them against another pair of polarized lenses - they are indeed polarized.  All-in-all, it's a good purchase if you're seeking a decent looking inexpensive pair of polarized sunglasses.

I went 4 stars instead of 5 because they are what I expected and what I was looking for but didn't knock my socks off in any special way.  I reserve my 5's for things I really love.

reviewText: My boyfriend loved this watch. I bought it back in  August of last year & it's still in good shape. He wears it at least 3 to 4 times a week.

I absolutely love the watch. I needed an inexpensive everyday watch and this is perfect. There were other reviewers who complained that it did not keep time properly, but I have not had that issue. I have had this almost a week and it is still keeping perfect time. It is a manual watch which means no batteries and you DO have to wind it. I actually like that idea! The watch looks great and I love the clear front and back to see the gears.

The only reason it is not a 5 star is the watch band is a little big for what was supposed to be a women't watch. I think my wrists are average size and I had to put in another notch since the smallest one was still too big and the heavy watch face would cause the watch to turn around on my wrist. Very annoying for someone who sits and types at a computer all day. Also the watch face was a lot larger than I thought it would be, but I have gotten used to it. If it was too small it would be pointless to have the clear front to see the inner workings.

For the money, it's a great watch! I wind it a little each day and so far no problems. Again, it has kept perfect time since I received it early this week and you just have to remember to wind it.

****UPDATE****
I did love the watch, but the pin broke that winds the watch and changes the hands. The pin is no longer locking properly and therefore the hands are not moving consistently. I am so very disappointed since I really did love this watch when I first got it. I made sure not to over wind the watch and was very careful with it. So, it was great at first, but now it's completely useless. Going to see if I can still return it.
Looks cheap and didn't realize it's a wind up before purchase.

reviewText: I'm only on day 2, but I really love this watch! Works like a charm. I don't care for the wrist strap, but that's an easy fix.

I think this watch is fantastic. You can see the cogs moving inside. I admit, mine didn't come with instructions, and in the land of electronic everything I didn't know how to set it. When it stopped, was when I saw how it worked. You pull out the crown to set it, then you push it in and wind the crown again, and it makes a little zippy noise and it goes! I cannot imagine why anyone would ever want a battery-operated watch. That was the reason why I never bought one, and I'm so happy I decided to buy a manual wind-up watch.
summary: I think this watch is fantastic. You can see the cogs moving inside

reviewText: I love love LOVE this watch! It has to be wound. No batteries. Excellent for storage. Just set it, wind it up and watch it go. It's cool how you can see it working inside. I bought a black watchband for it and it's gorgeous.

I received this watch piece to review. It was nicely packaged in a neat gift box.  It also came with a small gift card for personalization, however since is was obviously meant for Christmas giving I was unable to use it. I would suggest that a more generic gift card be included if that is to be an extra perk.  The watch itself was very nice looking and it was easy to set the time. I gave it as a gift to a young man for his 18 birthday. I removed the long chain it came with-- I thought it seemed cheap-- and attached it to a shorter brass "fob" that I purchased so it would be more useful as a pocket watch instead of a medallion. He seemed very pleased with the watch, though assuming he would be using it as an heirloom piece as suggested seemed a bit of a stretch.  Although it claims to be made of stainless steel, it has been made to look like brass, but feels much too lightweight, almost like more of a hard resin instead of metal, which takes away from its "antiquity" feel, in my opinion.  The one I received was embossed with the USS CONSTITUTION which was appropriate for my nephew who is a Navy dependent.  The fact that the watches are available in a variety of shapes and imprints-- some even being engraveable-  makes them ideal gift ideas for some. Time will tell if it, well-- keeps good time, which is pretty much the most important feature of a watch!  All said, the watch seems to be a nice and unique keepsake for the right person.
summary: A nice enough piece for the right person

reviewText: This is a nice watch for the price, well made, and keeps good time. This particular watch is stamped with the USS Constitution on it. It comes with a 16" chain which is fairly light weight, so that might need to be replaced at some point. Depending on how much it's used. The watch itself is 2inches wide. Pretty much the same as most pocket watches.  On the front of this watch , the USS Constitution is Stamped Boldly, on the back it is antiqued swirl finished brass. The watch opens from the top by the press of the top button.  To set the time, pull up on the top button and set the time then push it back down. Really simple.. great gift item. Comes in a gift wrapped box. So far since I've had it, it has kept time with my atomic clock.. Can't expect better than that..
summary: Eternity J. Unisex Antique 1797-1997 Pocket Watch USS Constitution

I was extremely disappointed with the dimensions and fabric quality.  The product description states "140 cm x 140 cm".  When I converted it to inches, it worked out to be 55" x 55 ".  I placed my order based on this dimension.  However, the actual measurements upon receipt are 77 " (length) x 28 " (wide).
Additionally, the computer image and product description show a "navy"/red mix; however, the actual real life image is BLACK/red.  The color issue was insignificant to me,and, I could have lived with that.

I also note that the material is more on the thin side which I feel is more appropriate for fall/spring as opposed to winter.  I have submitted a return request based on "inaccurate website description".  In this case, the seller bears the expense of the shipping charges due to their misrepresentation of the measurement and color description.  I will look elsewhere for a better quality, large size scarf as this is the SECOND "Made-in-China" scarf from Amazon that I am totally dissatisfied with.
summary: Gross Misrepresentation of Dimensions and Color

Couldn't live without these cubes anymore. You manage to organise all your stuff inside your suitcase/backpack in a way that makes travelling a whole new thing. Need to take something out at the airport? Just take out the box you need. No need to scrape your suitcase and messing all your clothes up while rushing at the safety check. You get to the hotel and you just take your cubes out and place them on a desk/floor/bed and always have your stuff organised and ready to pack back in. All in all - well impressed with the cubes, a great idea.

This is my first experience using packing cubes. The set I received is a set of 4, basically small, medium, large, and x-large. There is a little icon on the corner of each cube that shows what that size is intended for. You are of course welcome to put whatever you want in each cube. I found that I was able to keep my clothes folded neatly which resulted in less wrinkly clothes. However I did notice that I was not able to fit as much in my carry on (based on empty space left after cubes in). I can see it has its pros and cons to using packing cubes. The item itself was made of a nice nylon material. The zippers are nice, they glide smoothly and have ample material on the pull. Considering this is my first experience with packing cubes I would definitely use them again. This helps me avoid over packing (which for me is a good thing).

An Excellent High-Quality Kreisler Watch Band
This band is matte black and gave my smart watch a very strong and stealthy profile.  Its quality that you expect from Kreisler.  You can perform minor adjustments to the band with the included tool or remove links for a tighter fit.  Major adjustments would probably require a trip to the jeweler unless you have a specialized bracelet changing tool and/or a jewelers hammer/pin set.  Watch band tools are cheap on Amazon and a good investment if you are so inclined.  All-in-all, this is an excellent band at a very good price.

reviewText: Excellent band for my Pebble and a wonderful value compared to the alternatives proposed by Amazon.  The Kreisler unit is extremely well made and solid throughout.  I had to remove one link because my wrist is small and it was simple to do.  I used a small nail and by looking at the inside of the band the arrows point in the direction you need to push out the pin that holds the links together.  It was quick and simple. Another option was to go to the watch place at the mall and pay $5 for the adjustment.

This watch band is a replacement for the stock band that came with my MVMT chronograph.  It was a perfect fit.  I was able to make adjustments to the fit without removing links.  It would have been easy to remove a link by using a small nail or watch band tool.  The band provides an easy adjustment setting within the clasp.  This band is less expensive and of a higher quality than the ones offered by the company that made my watch.
summary: Reasonably Priced Easily Adjustable High Quality Band

reviewText:
I ordered this sheath lace dress in size Medium and color green. For reference, I'm 5'1", 125 lbs and measures 34, 29, 35. I just use the provided size chart in picking up my size and I think it worked out really well because I love how the dress fits me.

I think this is a very nice Spring or Summer dress. I love the green color of this dress. As for the style, this is a regular sheath dress with a zipper on the side. I didn't realize there was a zipper at first but eventually found it. I absolutely love the details at the back of the dress. It has this faux Chinese style button like ribbons button that are just really nice and gave the back of this dress an interesting look.

As for the fabric, this dress uses a lace fabric and a polyester lining I think. The lace is not the greatest but I think is good enough for the price. The fabric use for this dress is ok, is comfortable to wear and not scratchy like how cheaper lace sometimes feels against the skin. I washed this dress using delicate cycle settings and I place this inside a laundry bag to make sure the lace doesn't get caught in other clothing hardware like buttons or zippers. As for drying, I have dry this using low heat settings and line drying, although I prefer line drying for my clothes that are made in laces.

As for the workmanship, this dress looks neat on the outside. All the seams are neatly done and trimmed. However on the inner side of the dress, I can see some threads that needs trimming. So take note if you're very particular with details like this.

I received this product for free in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

The lace that is tied around the collar is a darker brown than the one in the picture and is just a normal piece of dark brown lace. I think the head band was the most well made even though the bow would slide off, but it was still better than the crap dress I received. I was very disappointed in this dress and I do not understand why it was given such good reviews by the other so called cosplayers.

Look: Picture tell it all, it is very shiny look. It is really obvious that one is wearing tights. I got a lot of compliments for this.

Overall Rating: At the price of 9 USD, for 5 wearings , the cost per wear on these is going to be under $2.00. You will not find another brand that feels this good, looks this good and costs this little. You will never look back and will fall in love with your legs all over again.

If you're a Harry Potter fan you should DEFINITELY GET THIS! It's awesome! It took a little while to arrive but that's perfectly okay. if you're getting it as a gift for someone then you will definitely want to order 30+ days in advance. The sooner the better just in case. It gives you an estimated time but I don't trust those 100%. They're a good ESTIMATE but not an exact promise. Anyways, the bracelet itself is beautiful and I'm extremely happy with it. Any Harry Potter fan will take one look at it and know exactly what the three separate charms mean. I don't understand how people are breaking theirs so easily. I have five bracelets like this one and another on its way. I've had them for an absolute minimum of 8 months (forgot to do reviews for a lot of the things I purchased haha) and I've worn ALL of them multiple times and never had an issue. Then again I'm smart enough to know I need to be gentle with "cheap" jewelry. Some people just don't think things through. Be gentle and you'll have no problem - at least not for a very long time. And sure accidents do happen but I really do believe most of these people are being too rough and quick. The chain has multiple loops to latch onto so it will fit different wrist sizes as well. I have a wrist between petite and average and it fits just fine.

I do like this necklace because it does NOT look like I paid $1.50 for it. However the leaves do not stay in place for very long. They're not connected to one another so after walking around they eventually slip apart so that one leaf is up against your throat and the other is dangling down between your breasts. It is something that can very easily be fixed though. You can easily use a small dab of super glue to connect the pieces together in any way you choose. it does defeat the style of this necklace but considering it does not look cheap and looks as if I actually spent $20 or more on it, I'd say a dab of super glue is totally worth it. For that reason I DO RECOMMEND this necklace. long as you don't mind constantly readjusting or gluing it in whatever specific way you want.
Sorry for the blurry pictures. Didn't feel like doing it over and over again so that's what you get. Just showing you how it's "supposed" to look and what happens after a few minutes. Also you can see some of the silver rusted so here's some advice...
***** ADVICE ***** With ALL cheap jewelry you get you absolutely must put on a clear coat of nail polish (doesn't have to be expensive; I just use a 99cent bottle) so that the color doesn't fade - so it remains shiny. Also, the clear coat will make sure your skin doesn't turn green. Don't slop it on! You only need a small amount, a regular layer evenly distributed. Don't rush it either. Take your time. Do half the chain, hang it from a table, let it dry, do the other half, etc. I put a clear coat on my jewelry every 6 months to a year depending on how often its worn, if I went swimming with it on, been in the sun all day, etc. Those things make me put it on even more.
summary: I DO recommend BUT read my review first!

reviewText:
I was very happy with this product upon first getting it! The materials are sturdy and good quality, nothing fancy, basic & durable which is what I wanted! I couldn't wait to get it on! And it wasn't bad I guess for not being laced very tight last night when I wore it for an hour to start seasoning it. Well this morning I went to put it on again for day 2 of seasoning. I had a bit more time to spend with it and I went a bit tighter. Now I'm not as happy with it!.. I re-laced it so it was right, put it on & tightened it up. I got my waist down an inch and a half but when I look in the mirror the bottom almost can't go any tighter and I don't even have an inch up top or a half inch in middle to go tighter... so it's a size 29 instead of 26..... big difference.... I was supposed to be able to lace down up to 5 inches and it only goes s max of 2.... the boning IS plastic after all not spiral steel boning... besides the front edges where the hooks and buttons are and the back edge where it laces, the description said it had 22 steel double bones... (so we're up to 2 disappointments now..) and to "top" it off.. the bottom won't lay down flat on its own.... so I'm trying to train it to lay down flat with a wide sash tied around the bottom edge.. and idk... guess i wasted my money & I'll have to get another.... pretty disappointed...
I'm my pictures you can see it's of good quality and looks great! But you can also see that there's hardly any lacing left and my sash around the bottom... then the side-view picture without the sash.... it doesn't show how the sides poof up, which I'd be fine with if the front didn't stick out like that..

I received two of these as a gift, the red and the blue. The blue fell apart immediately, and the red Well, I pried it apart with my fingernails. Why? Well, for starters, the two acrylic rhinestones inside each weren't attached to one another, so by swapping them I was able to have two pendants which were both blue on one side and red on the other. The other reason? So I could attempt to glue them together more securely. I mean, if one came apart in the package, it was only a matter of time for the other.

My first attempt at repair was straight-up super glue. This worked flawlessly to bind the rhinestones together (Which by the way were somehow all scratched up, but not noticeably from a distance) but didn't work on the metal piece so much. When I used nail polish remover to remove the glue residue so I could try something difference (Nail polish remover is the only thing that can dissolve super glue) the cheap paint on the pendants began dissolving faster than the glue, exposing the raw copper underneath. Well. This is lovely. Hey, maybe I can remove all the paint on purpose and use a silver plating kit on the remaining copper! maybe. OK, most people aren't as handy as me, and wouldnt have a silver plating kit just sitting in their toolbox. But whatever. Thats something I haven't gotten to trying just yet.

The one that was more salvageable (as in there was no super glue residue in a noticeable place) Ive sealed back together with epoxy and attached to a short leather necklace via a brass chainmail link. The nice contrast that the gold and jewel make with the leather makes it look a dozen times more authentic than the garbage chain it came with; I wear it as standard jewelry and not a costume piece, and get compliments on it all the time. If I want it to be red or blue, I just flip it over. Easy-peasy.

Still. It should have been in wearable condition and not falling apart to begin with. I should not have had to get creative with epoxy and super glue and Wal-Mart craft department supplies to make the piece presentable. The jewels should not have been all scratched up!

DO NOT BUY THIS unless you have the means by which to do at-home jewelry repair, because it WILL BREAK.
summary: DO NOT BUY THIS unless you have the means by which to do at-home jewelry repair, because it WILL BREAK.

The legs are way too short and the arms are longer, especially compared to the legs. My son has bigger legs (chub rolls) so I was not able to snap it closed. He also has really long legs and had high waters in this outfit, but the sleeves were long where I would need to roll them up. I've posted a couple pictures as examples.

4th: care tag recommends dry cleaning, who has time for that?!?! Especially for children's clothes?!?!

Lastly, the size is not listed anywhere on this outfit, it's not on any of the tags attached to it or the paper store tags, I had to check my Amazon order to confirm what size I bought.

I will be returned this outfit.

reviewText:
I've wanted this running top ever since I saw it on clearance last year at a local retailer. It definitely stands out aesthetically and feels high-quality (like most Nike products do). It is quite warm and the only thing that kept me from pulling the trigger on it last year was that there was no zipper in front to help control ventilation.

I haven't used it yet but will update when I do. Judging by its weight, I'm guessing it will be most appropriate for temperatures in the high-30s to low-50s (while running, absent windchill).

UPDATE: I finally had the opportunity to use it tonight and it worked great. 44 degrees F with a moderate wind or of the south. I started out going north and was comfortable during my warm-up walk sweated a little during the run but was still comfortable. I felt the same on the way back despite the wind.

For comparison, the temp last week was ten degrees cooler with a strong wind and there was no way this would've ever cut it. (I used a heavier weight top from another brand and that just barely sufficed.) So, my initial estimate was pretty spot-on. I'll update again as I use it more.
summary: I can't believe this item isn't more popular

The description for this item states that it is a "tiny" butterfly necklace with an 18 inch chain. I received this item in the mail, and when the description says tiny, it is accurate. The butterfly itself is is only 1/4 inch by 1/4 inch, and will fit inside a dime. The necklace measures just under 8 inches when held by the clasp, so the total length isn't 18 inches, it's just under 16 inches. I've added a picture to show the size of the butterfly in comparison to a dime.

Luckily, I was purchasing this for my 7 year old daughter, who absolutely adores it. It is small and feminine, not too shiny and so far it's been durable enough for a 7 year old to wear it without breaking. The clasp is easy to open and close and the butterfly doesn't "flip over" during wear. The necklace is the perfect gift for a young lady, but seems a bit small to me, for a full grown woman.

Disclaimer: I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review. I have provided my review and the star rating based on my personal experience, which is not affected by the cost of the item. I have no affiliation with the company or its employees and always welcome feedback, positive and negative and questions.

Tiny is misleading...it's a fairly average size pendant, suitable for kids and adults!

I'm not a statement jewelry person and prefer to buy fairly inexpensive silver toned necklaces with small pendants that I can layer or switch out frequently - oh and I also love butterflies!  I was hesitant to buy this since there were no reviews, but I received a discount on the necklace for my own review, so I took the plunge!

The necklace was Prime eligible and arrived in 2 days.  This is pretty rare for Amazon jewelry at this price point, I usually find it comes from overseas and takes weeks to get.  It arrived in a huge lightly padded envelope which offered very little protection and is a waste of materials.  Luckily, the necklace was safe and sound, sealed in a small plastic baggie with a cute business card/thank you from the seller, who is a small California based business.

The necklace arrived twisted with a small knot, so I fixed that up and noticed instantly how SHORT the chain was.  I only wear 18-21" chains and I knew immediately this was not the 18" that was promised in the product description.  I measured it and it came in under 16".  It was almost a choker on me.  However, both the chain and the butterly are lightweight and comfortable.  The butterfly sits nicely without constantly flipping over and the wings are soft, rounded edges, so it is comfortable to wear.  I just switched the pendant out to another chain.  The chain itself isn't bad.  Basic chain that you find with most costume pendant necklaces.  The clasp is easy to open/close and is secure.

The butterfly itself is adorable!  It is not quite as shiny as I saw online, which I prefer, because it gives it a nicer look.  The metal (it is described as bronze) does not bend or misshape and the detail on the butterfly is pretty.  I am glad that the butterfly isn't tiny. It is dainty and perfect for a simple look.

 It is appx 1/4" x 1/4" for people like me that don't measure in millimeters.

For the price, the detail of the butterfly and the 2 day prime shipping, this was a great buy and I will wear the butterfly often this summer on another chain and on a charm bracelet.  However, minus 2 stars as the chain was 2+"  shorter than described and a better packaging solution would offer more protection to the item and less waste (no loss of stars for packaging).  I hope seller fixes the description of the chain size to match the actual product.

reviewText:
My four year old just brought me the scraps of this necklace from her room and reminded me how sad this necklace made her - which compelled me to write a review.
My four year old was disappointed every time this broke.  Which was three times.  In the first two days.  The first day she wore it, it literally fell off her neck.  The chain just snapped in two.  She wasn't roughhousing.  She was standing.  My daughter cried.  My husband relinked the chain.
Later that day the link attached to the charm snapped in two and the charm completely fell off when my daughter was sitting.  She cried again. My husband reattached it with parts from a fishing lure.  At school the next day the chain clasp broke.  Again, the necklace fell to the ground.  She cried.  Do not purchase this product.  You'll save a few bucks and a lot of tears.
summary: How to make your little girl cry - and not in a good way - buy this necklace.

When I saw the package containing my Kingsize Men's Big & Tall Hanes Brief 3-Pack on the front porch my buttocks began to clench frantically in anticipation of the comfort the briefs would soon provide to them. I grabbed the package and started to tear it open as I rushed into my house.  I removed the briefs from the excellent container provided for them noticing the underwear had not been damaged from the stress of shipping. In fact the briefs were packaged in not one, but two tough plastic coverings the outer envelope being opaque- ostensively to prevent salacious simpering by cretinous couriers.

I freed the briefs from their protective covering, stripped down and tugged the underwear past my knees and onto my midsection.  I tried all three briefs on, with all fitting superbly, when my wife, by clearing her throat, made me aware I had not made it into my bedroom, but had become naked and tried on the underwear in the living room while my wife was hosting a party for some ponzi schemed purveyor of plastic products or other.  A few of the mature women and one of the men present oohed and awed as I presented by birthday suit, however the majority shrugged and ignored me.  I grabbed up my briefs possessively and scampered off to my bedroom to bask in the enjoyment of my Kingsize Men's Big & Tall Hanes Brief 3-Pack collection of underwear.

reviewText:
I bought a size 1 for my Son who is somewhere between a 12 and 13, and a size 11 for my daughter who is a solid size 9(toddler) right now. Both pairs of shoes fit with some room to grow but because of the back strap, they do not come off. Once the kids otgrow the back strap, it can be moved forward and they will be able to get some more time out of them. (They will get lots of use before the kids grow out of them)

The last set that we bought had the lining on the outside a bit as well as the inside and they always had leaves and whatever else from outside all over them. I like that these have the same soft lining, but only on the inside. My kids both still love them and it does not appear that they are any less comfortable.

We spend a lot of time outside and do a lot of camping and bonfires and my kids like to have slippers to wear for these events. Running around outside would wreck most slippers, so I've pretty much fallen in love with these. They're cozy on the inside but the outside is easy to clean so I can just wash them off and they're like new again. After a rinse off and a towel dry, the kids can still wear them around the house without leaving a mess.

I could rave forever about these. They are one of a select few products that I will keep on replacing as my kids grow out of them because they are so perfect for out needs and they just make life easier. I would absolutely recommend. And, after having bought the ones that have the fuzzy exterior as well, I would recommend these first if your kids will ever wear them out of the house.
summary: One of my absolute favorite kid products - makes my life much easier and worth every penny!

Size L was listed as 48", but I'm measuring it at just 45".  No excuse for measurements being off by 3".

This is a very well constructed belt.  The belt strap is thick and having the end finished with leather is very sharp!  However, I ordered a 45 inch belt - a medium, but received a 43 inch belt - a small.  The belt when laid flat on a counter measures 43 inches from end to end, including the D-rings.  Fortunately, it is still long enough to use, but is a little harder to tighten for best comfort.  After reading other reviews, it seems these belts are shorter than advertised, so you may want to subtract two inches from the length they say it is.  Otherwise, this is a very nice belt, and am happy with it.  Will probably order another one in a different color.

For your reference, I wear 32 or 33 inch waist jeans, and this belt (the medium), when tightened for best fit, has about 3 inches of strap beyond the buckle.
summary: Great Belt, but Shorter than Advertised
